  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Periodic leg movement disorder is defined as periodic episodes of repetitive limb movements&#xD;
      during sleep that mainly occur in the lower limb, including the hips, knees and toes and&#xD;
      sometimes affects the upper limb. It may be accompanied by frequent nocturnal arousals, and&#xD;
      if so, this sleep disturbance may cause excessive daytime sleepiness. Chronic kidney disease&#xD;
      patients are at risk of periodic leg movements and common causes are iron deficiency, anemia,&#xD;
      raised serum calcium and central and peripheral nervous system disorders.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
